This paper deals with the problem of localizing type errors in programming languages, which is a core concern of programming language research. The paper proposes a data-driven approach to error localization based on supervised learning, which involves analyzing a large corpus of training data to automatically learn a model of where the error is most likely to be found. This approach involves several subfields of computer science, including programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SE), machine learning (cs.LG), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, given that the paper focuses on programming language analysis and error localization, cs.PL is the most likely sub-category.
